steps.instruction:
### Steps
1. Preheat oven to 400F
2. Cut butter into small cubes; place them in a small bowl to soften
3. Peel potatoes, carrots and parsnips
4. Cut them into 1 inch cubes and place in a medium bowl
5. Toss veggies with oil, salt, pepper and cayenne pepper
6. Transfer to a 13x9 inch baking dish
7. Bake for 10 minutes
8. Add apple crisp mix to butter
9. Blend with fork until crumbly
10. Remove veggies from oven
11. Stir in raisins
12. Top with the butter mixture
13. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes
